<div id="review_682721264" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/682721264" />
    <a title="April Hesler" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/17559214-april-hesler"><img alt="April Hesler" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1403672736p2/17559214.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/682721264?book_show_action=true">Jul 31, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="April Hesler" class="user" itemprop="url" name="April Hesler" href="/user/show/17559214-april-hesler">April Hesler</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer682721264" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3442212931935556943">I&apos;m giving this book 3 stars firstly because of the editing errors, and secondly because it&apos;s an incredible amount to take in. It goes from zero to sixty in a matter of a chapter. <br/>One minute Whitney is dealing with normal teenager high school drama, the next she&apos;s trying to figure out how to save the world. Honestly there&apos;s nothing wrong with switching fears so fast, it&apos;s just the way it was done. Once you learn Whitney&apos;s fate or role, however you want to look at it, the information you receive </span>
  <span id="freeText3442212931935556943" style="display:none">I'm giving this book 3 stars firstly because of the editing errors, and secondly because it's an incredible amount to take in. It goes from zero to sixty in a matter of a chapter. <br />One minute Whitney is dealing with normal teenager high school drama, the next she's trying to figure out how to save the world. Honestly there's nothing wrong with switching fears so fast, it's just the way it was done. Once you learn Whitney's fate or role, however you want to look at it, the information you receive comes in quick, and it's laid on thick to the point you're completely bored. I almost quit reading a few times because it was putting me to sleep. I actually took a nap. <br />Great storyline, wonderful story telling, the details about the era are spot on. I'll continue the series, I just hope it's a little more action now that everything has been explained</span>
  <a data-text-id="3442212931935556943" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


