<span id="freeTextContainer8339868002041130708">Whitney Forbes isn&apos;t your average nearly-sixteen-year-old girl. And Reid Wallace isn&apos;t your average teenage boy either. <br/><br/>Whitney has ESP along with several other gifts. She knows of Reid&apos;s reputation, but is slightly curious when he turns his attention towards her instead of Liz Cooley. <br/><br/>I can&apos;t say much more without giving the plot away. I absolutely loved this book and could barely put down my Kindle. Though I didn&apos;t understand hardly any of the scientific aspects of the book, the background sto</span>
  <span id="freeText8339868002041130708" style="display:none">Whitney Forbes isn't your average nearly-sixteen-year-old girl. And Reid Wallace isn't your average teenage boy either. <br /><br />Whitney has ESP along with several other gifts. She knows of Reid's reputation, but is slightly curious when he turns his attention towards her instead of Liz Cooley. <br /><br />I can't say much more without giving the plot away. I absolutely loved this book and could barely put down my Kindle. Though I didn't understand hardly any of the scientific aspects of the book, the background story of Whitney's and Reid's attraction is just as enticing as what they learn about each other and what they're to do in a world that no longer seems safe. <br /><br />I can't WAIT to read the second book in the summer!</span>
